results.title: Live Love Beach Pendulum Clock
results.description:
Live Love Beach Pendulum Clock;
This clock features a beachy twist on the common phrase, "Live Laugh Love". When you are at the beach, you say, "Live Love BEACH"!

All clocks are made to order in my studio in rural Ohio. 3 Pendulum clock sizes are available. Only the best quartz clock movements are used. The clocks are tested for 24hrs before they are shipped. 2-AA batteries are required.

Production Process- Clocks are produced with fade resistant inks. The artwork is carefully mounted onto a laser cut, 1/4" thick MDF panel. A special UV resistant coating is applied for a durable finish. Dependable quartz clock movements are used. Clock hands are aged to match the antique vintage look of the clock.

HOW TO ORDER
To order this clock just choose your size, click the "add to cart" button and proceed to the checkout page.

Star Track(s) – The Rex Generation
A new T.V. series from the Fountain of Goof (F.O.G. T.v.) Network

Season 1

Episode 1:  
WTF Just Happened? Captain's Log Date – The Future.  While trekking thru time, Captain Querk realizes that his entire crew just started speaking in pig-latin.

Episode 2:  
The Land of Logic – An Unsolved Anomolie – Solved.  Spook discovers a mysterious looking, black and white object floating aimlessly thru space.  As the vessel travels closer, the crew sees that it resembles a very large rat tagged “Mickey".

Bones:  “He’s Dead Jim”.

Episode 3:  
A search team is beamed down to a seemingly uninhabitable world – unexpectedly greeted by an alien, jeweled species called “The Kardashians”.  The crew immediately figures it’s a backed-up “Booby” trap and returns to the ship to report their “Findings”.

Episode 4:  
The Morgue – “Resistance is Futile."  Conversations with an alien culture that has a mindset of immortality.

Episode 5: 
Traveling at Warp Weed: Returning to a 1960’s memorable psychedelic trip...a crew member shares fond memories of space...between his ears...

Episode 6:  
"Nobody’s Home" – When Captain Querk and his crew returns to earth, he is utterly astonished to see mankind going ape-shit with anger, hatred and violence.  A WTF happened crazy moment that ends...back to the beginning:  Star Tracks – The Rex Generation.
